> 
> Thanks for flagging [@szhsin](https://github.com/szhsin). Looks like there's a bug in the messaging here. If you aren't using Turbopack, you can set an explicit root directory via [outputFileTracingRoot](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/config/next-config-js/output#caveats) which should silence the warning.

This worked. The warning did not appear after setting:
```
const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  outputFileTracingRoot: __dirname,
};
```

For those using `next.config.mjs` , the correct version of the above is

```typescript
/**
 * @type {import('next').NextConfig}
 */
const nextConfig = {
  outputFileTracingRoot: import.meta.dirname,
};
```

